value.value: Adult intrinsic neuron with ipsilateral arbors in a single VNC neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a primary neuron of the 13A hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the leg neuropil and sends output to the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is gaba (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 5 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere, metathoracic neuromere and prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
